# .gitleaksignore
#
# Use this file to suppress specific findings that are confirmed false positives.
# Each line is a SHA256 fingerprint of a finding — gitleaks prints these when it
# reports a secret. Copy the fingerprint here to silence it permanently.
#
# Format:
#   <fingerprint>  # optional human-readable note
#
# How to get a fingerprint:
#   gitleaks detect -f json -r /tmp/report.json
#   cat /tmp/report.json | python3 -m json.tool | grep Fingerprint
#
# Example (not real — replace with actual fingerprints from your scan):
#   abc123def456...  # fake AWS key in docs/examples/aws-config-example.md
#
# IMPORTANT: Only add fingerprints for values you have personally verified
# are not real secrets. Never add a fingerprint just to make CI pass.
